						               													<description>You take the role of an adorable kitty-lover granny.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your mission is to get as many kitties as possible with the help of your granny friends, avoid the health inspector, suffer diseases and deal with the Death.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Grannies and the kitties are grouped into five categories.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player get 5 Grannies cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each turn appears a kitty and the player who has more compatible grannies with the kitty gets the kitty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player doesn't have any compatible granny card they have to get a disease card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In case of a tie, the player who doesn't have a disease card compatible with the kitty wins the kitty.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a tie persists the kitty remains on the table and another turn is played, the winner takes both kitties.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a Player wins a kitty can use a Health inspector card from their own deck against another player. If this player doesn't have a bribe card they has to give 3 kitties cards from their own pile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the death card appears the players can discard their diseases cards, discarding a compatible grannie (both card are discarded).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when all the kitties cards are gone.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who gets more kitties cards wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
